"title": "5743: widows",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5743",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's tender concern for bereaved wives is declared throughout the whole of Scripture. He defends their rights and expects his people to do the same.</p>\n<h2>God is the protector of widows</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:5\">PSA 68:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:18\">DEU 10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:9\">PSA 146:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:25\">PRO 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:11\">JER 49:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's concern for widows</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:41-Mark12:44\">MRK 12:41–12:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:1-Luke21:4\">LUK 21:1–21:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:11-Luke7:15\">LUK 7:11–7:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:1-Luke18:5\">LUK 18:1–18:5</a></p>\n<h2>Widows are to be treated justly</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:19\">DEU 27:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:22-Exod22:24\">EXO 22:22–22:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:21-Job24:22\">JOB 24:21–24:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:6\">PSA 94:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:4\">ISA 10:1–10:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:3-Jer22:5\">JER 22:3–22:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:25\">EZK 22:25</a></p>\n<h2>Widows are not to be exploited</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:22\">EXO 22:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:2\">ISA 10:1–10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:7\">EZK 22:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:5\">MAL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:38-Mark12:40\">MRK 12:38–12:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:45-Luke20:47\">LUK 20:45–20:47</a></p>\n<h2>The law requires God's people to provide for widows</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:19\">DEU 24:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:28-Deut14:29\">DEU 14:28–14:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:11\">DEU 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:17\">DEU 24:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:20-Deut24:21\">DEU 24:20–24:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:12\">DEU 26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:17\">ISA 1:17</a> <em>The prophet encourages God's people to return to the law.</em></p>\n<h2>The Christian community are to care for widows</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:3\">1TI 5:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:4-1Tim5:16\">1TI 5:4–5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:8-1Cor7:9\">1CO 7:8–7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:27\">JAS 1:27</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of widows and their treatment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:14\">DEU 16:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:16-Ruth1:17\">RUT 1:16–1:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:13-1Kgs17:14\">1KI 17:13–17:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:3\">JOB 24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:13\">JOB 29:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:36-Luke2:38\">LUK 2:36–2:38</a> <em>Anna</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:25-Luke4:26\">LUK 4:25–4:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:11-Luke7:17\">LUK 7:11–7:17</a> <em>the widow of Nain</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:1\">ACT 6:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:36-Acts9:41\">ACT 9:36–9:41</a> <em>Dorcas</em></p>\n<h2>Women widowed because of God's judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:22-Exod22:24\">EXO 22:22–22:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:9\">PSA 109:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:17\">ISA 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:8\">JER 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:3\">LAM 5:3</a></p>\n<h2>Laws governing the remarriage of widows</h2>\n<h3>The people generally</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:5-Deut25:10\">DEU 25:5–25:10</a></strong> <em>The OT emphasises continuity of the family line.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:8\">GEN 38:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:12\">RUT 3:12</a> <em>Boaz refers to the law which gave the nearest male relative the duty of marrying the widow</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:10\">RUT 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:19\">MRK 12:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:28\">LUK 20:28</a></p>\n<h3>The priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:13-Lev21:14\">LEV 21:13–21:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:22\">EZK 44:22</a></p>\n<h2>Widowhood as the personification of a city</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:1\">LAM 1:1</a></strong> <em>A lament for desolate Jerusalem.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:4-Isa54:5\">ISA 54:4–54:5</a> <em>a prophecy of the restoration of Jerusalem</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:7\">REV 18:7</a> <em>the boasts of Babylon</em></p>",
